description: Tiger Woods received a special sponsor exemption due to his "exceptional lifetime achievement" of 82 wins, which makes him eligible to play in the tour's signature events.
title: Tiger Woods receives PGA Tour exemption for signature events due to 'exceptional lifetime achievement'

description: "America's Got Talent" judge Howie Mandel clarified that his wife Terry was not drunk but instead high on marijuana gummies when she took a bloody fall in Las Vegas.
title: 'America's Got Talent' judge Howie Mandel says wife was high on marijuana gummies, not drunk before accident

description: New York Giants rookie Malik Nabers hasn't had his NFL debut yet, but he's already got some beef with Dallas Cowboys cornerback Trevon Diggs.
title: Giants rookie Malik Nabers already trolling division rival before making debut

description: A Florida landlord was charged with killing a family of four, including two children, and burning their remains in the fire pit of the home, police said.
title: Florida landlord killed family of 4, burned bodies in fire pit: police

description: A record viewership night for the WNBA prompted Republican Texas Sen. Ted Cruz to call out the out the USA Basketball selection committee for Caitlin Clark's Olympic snub.
title: Ted Cruz calls out Caitlin Clark Olympic snub after WNBA records most-watched game in 23 years
